(46, 1, '2026-07-12 18:19:03', '2026-07-12 12:19:03', '<h1>🔨 Premium Auction Listing: Vintage Charizard Card</h1>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>📋 Item Overview</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>Item Title:</strong> 1999 Pokémon Base Set Charizard Holo (1st Edition / Shadowless / Unlimited Variant)</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Card Number:</strong> 4/102</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Rarity:</strong> Holofoil Rare</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Era:</strong> Vintage Classic (Wizards of the Coast Era)</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Estimated Value:</strong> Market Value / Appraisal Available Upon Request</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>🔍 Detailed Description</h2>\r\n<p>Up for absolute auction is the undisputed holy grail of the trading card world: the <strong>Vintage Base Set Charizard Holofoil</strong>. First released in 1999 by Wizards of the Coast, this iconic piece of pop-culture history defined a generation and continues to serve as the gold standard for alternative asset investments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Featuring the legendary, fierce artwork by <strong>Mitsuhiro Arita</strong>, this specific card captures the brilliant, vibrant holographic background that collectors have spent over two decades chasing. Whether you are looking to anchor a high-end investment portfolio or crown a lifelong nostalgic collection, this Charizard represents a rare opportunity to own a foundational piece of gaming history.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>📊 Key Specifications & Condition</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Card Details</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>Set:</strong> Base Set (1999)</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Type:</strong> Fire / Stage 2 Evolution</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Attack Power:</strong> Fire Spin (100 Damage) / Energy Burn Ability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Professional Grading & Condition Report</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>Grading Authority:</strong> Available raw or pre-screened (Please check specific lot sub-variants for PSA/BGS/CGC certification numbers).</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Front Surface:</strong> Excellent centering, sharp registration, crisp holofoil gloss with minimal to no micro-scratching.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Back Surface:</strong> Deep, rich blue pigments with clean borders.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Edges & Corners:</strong> Sharp cuts, minimal edge-wear or whitening typical of careful preservation inside heavy-duty top-loaders or archival vaults.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>📈 Investment Potential & Provenance</h2>\r\n<p>The Vintage Base Set Charizard is not simply a trading card; it is a blue-chip historical artifact. Over the last decade, high-grade vintage Charizards have consistently outperformed traditional market indices, breaking records at major auction houses globally.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>Scarcity:</strong> As time progresses, uncirculated and pristine copies of this 1999 release become increasingly difficult to locate.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Cultural Impact:</strong> As the mascot of <em>Pokémon Red</em> and the most recognizable creature in the franchise, Charizard commands a global premium unmatched by any other pocket monster.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>📦 Shipping, Handling & Security</h2>\r\n<p>Given the high-value nature of this auction item, the following strict logistics protocols will apply:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li><strong>Archival Packaging:</strong> The card is housed in a brand new, acid-free penny sleeve, inserted into a rigid premium top-loader, and sealed inside a waterproof team bag.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Secure Transport:</strong> Shipped via a crush-proof, heavily padded box (never a flimsy bubble mailer).</li>\r\n  <li><strong>White-Glove Delivery:</strong> Fully insured transit with signature confirmation required upon delivery. International tracking and customs clearance management are provided.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>💬 Bidder Notes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>Inspection:</strong> Please review the high-resolution, unedited photography accompanying this listing carefully before placing your bids.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Questions:</strong> Click \"Contact Seller\" or \"Ask Auctioneer\" for specific high-res scans or additional condition verification.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Vintage Charizard Card', 'Up for auction is the crown jewel of pop-culture collectibles: the legendary 1999 Wizards of the Coast Base Set Charizard Holofoil. Featuring the iconic, fierce artwork by Mitsuhiro Arita, this timeless card is both the ultimate nostalgic grail and a premiere blue-chip alternative asset. Kept in exceptional, well-preserved condition with crisp holographic gloss, this brilliant specimen is ready to anchor a high-end investment portfolio or take center stage in a master collection. Don\'t miss your chance to own gaming royalty—bid today!', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'vintage-charizard-card', '', '', '2026-07-12 18:19:20', '2026-07-12 12:19:20', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?post_type=product&#038;p=46', 0, 'product', '', 0),
(47, 1, '2026-07-12 18:19:24', '2026-07-12 12:19:24', '<h1>🔨 Premium Auction Listing: Vintage Charizard Card</h1>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>📋 Item Overview</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Item Title:</strong> 1999 Pokémon Base Set Charizard Holo (1st Edition / Shadowless / Unlimited Variant)</li>\n  <li><strong>Card Number:</strong> 4/102</li>\n  <li><strong>Rarity:</strong> Holofoil Rare</li>\n  <li><strong>Era:</strong> Vintage Classic (Wizards of the Coast Era)</li>\n  <li><strong>Estimated Value:</strong> Market Value / Appraisal Available Upon Request</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>🔍 Detailed Description</h2>\n<p>Up for absolute auction is the undisputed holy grail of the trading card world: the <strong>Vintage Base Set Charizard Holofoil</strong>. First released in 1999 by Wizards of the Coast, this iconic piece of pop-culture history defined a generation and continues to serve as the gold standard for alternative asset investments.</p>\n\n<p>Featuring the legendary, fierce artwork by <strong>Mitsuhiro Arita</strong>, this specific card captures the brilliant, vibrant holographic background that collectors have spent over two decades chasing. Whether you are looking to anchor a high-end investment portfolio or crown a lifelong nostalgic collection, this Charizard represents a rare opportunity to own a foundational piece of gaming history.</p>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>📊 Key Specifications & Condition</h2>\n\n<h3>Card Details</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Set:</strong> Base Set (1999)</li>\n  <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>\n  <li><strong>Type:</strong> Fire / Stage 2 Evolution</li>\n  <li><strong>Attack Power:</strong> Fire Spin (100 Damage) / Energy Burn Ability</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Professional Grading & Condition Report</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Grading Authority:</strong> Available raw or pre-screened (Please check specific lot sub-variants for PSA/BGS/CGC certification numbers).</li>\n  <li><strong>Front Surface:</strong> Excellent centering, sharp registration, crisp holofoil gloss with minimal to no micro-scratching.</li>\n  <li><strong>Back Surface:</strong> Deep, rich blue pigments with clean borders.</li>\n  <li><strong>Edges & Corners:</strong> Sharp cuts, minimal edge-wear or whitening typical of careful preservation inside heavy-duty top-loaders or archival vaults.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>📈 Investment Potential & Provenance</h2>\n<p>The Vintage Base Set Charizard is not simply a trading card; it is a blue-chip historical artifact. Over the last decade, high-grade vintage Charizards have consistently outperformed traditional market indices, breaking records at major auction houses globally.</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Scarcity:</strong> As time progresses, uncirculated and pristine copies of this 1999 release become increasingly difficult to locate.</li>\n  <li><strong>Cultural Impact:</strong> As the mascot of <em>Pokémon Red</em> and the most recognizable creature in the franchise, Charizard commands a global premium unmatched by any other pocket monster.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>📦 Shipping, Handling & Security</h2>\n<p>Given the high-value nature of this auction item, the following strict logistics protocols will apply:</p>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Archival Packaging:</strong> The card is housed in a brand new, acid-free penny sleeve, inserted into a rigid premium top-loader, and sealed inside a waterproof team bag.</li>\n  <li><strong>Secure Transport:</strong> Shipped via a crush-proof, heavily padded box (never a flimsy bubble mailer).</li>\n  <li><strong>White-Glove Delivery:</strong> Fully insured transit with signature confirmation required upon delivery. International tracking and customs clearance management are provided.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>💬 Bidder Notes</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Inspection:</strong> Please review the high-resolution, unedited photography accompanying this listing carefully before placing your bids.</li>\n  <li><strong>Questions:</strong> Click \"Contact Seller\" or \"Ask Auctioneer\" for specific high-res scans or additional condition verification.</li>\n</ul>', 'Vintage Charizard Card', 'Up for auction is the crown jewel of pop-culture collectibles: the legendary 1999 Wizards of the Coast Base Set Charizard Holofoil. Featuring the iconic, fierce artwork by Mitsuhiro Arita, this timeless card is both the ultimate nostalgic grail and a premiere blue-chip alternative asset. Kept in exceptional, well-preserved condition with crisp holographic gloss, this brilliant specimen is ready to anchor a high-end investment portfolio or take center stage in a master collection. Don\'t miss your chance to own gaming royalty—bid today!', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '46-autosave-v1', '', '', '2026-07-12 18:19:24', '2026-07-12 12:19:24', '', 46, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=47', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
