(70, 1, '2026-07-13 15:52:31', '2026-07-13 09:52:31', '<h2>📋 Vehicle Overview</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>Year / Make / Model:</strong> 1967 Chevrolet Corvette Sting Ray Convertible</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Engine:</strong> 427 cu in (7.0L) L71 Big-Block V8 (435 HP Tri-Power)</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Transmission:</strong> Muncie M21 Close-Ratio 4-Speed Manual</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Exterior Color:</strong> Marina Blue with Black Stinger Hood Stripe</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Interior Color:</strong> Bright Blue Vinyl / Leather Seating Surfaces</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Mileage:</strong> 1,245 miles (Since complete frame-off restoration)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>🔍 Detailed Description</h2>\r\n<p>Up for absolute auction is the pinnacle of American muscle and automotive styling: the <strong>1967 Chevrolet Corvette Sting Ray Convertible</strong>. Universally regarded as the most refined and desirable year of the C2 generation, this specific example features the legendary, high-performance <strong>L71 427 Big-Block engine</strong> topped with the famous \"Tri-Power\" triple two-barrel carburetor setup, generating an astonishing factory-rated 435 horsepower.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finished in striking, factory-correct Marina Blue, this classic Vette underwent an uncompromising, multi-year, rotisserie frame-off restoration to NCRS (National Corvette Restorers Society) standards. Every detail—from the iconic, aggressive black stinger hood to the roaring side-mount exhaust system—has been perfectly dialed in. This vehicle looks, drives, and sounds exactly as it did when it rolled off the St. Louis assembly line in 1967, offering an unrepeatable opportunity for serious automotive investors and collectors alike.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>📊 Features & Mechanical Condition</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>Drivetrain:</strong> Original, numbers-matching L71 427/435 HP V8 block, correct intake manifold, and Tri-Power carburetors. Power is delivered to the pavement via a heavy-duty Positraction rear differential.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Exterior & Trim:</strong> Flawless Marina Blue paint polished to a mirror finish. Brand new, correct white convertible soft top and a immaculate chrome bumper package. Equipped with iconic 15-inch turbine-style bolt-on wheels wrapped in redline tires.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Interior:</strong> Fully restored cabin featuring correct blue bucket seats, factory AM/FM radio, telescoping steering wheel, and fully functional, crisp dashboard instrumentation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>📜 Provenance & Documentation</h2>\r\n<p>To preserve your investment, this Corvette is accompanied by an extensive historical file:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Original Tank Sticker (Order Copy) validated and preserved.</li>\r\n  <li>Complete photo-documentation folder detailing the step-by-step frame-off restoration process.</li>\r\n  <li>A thick binder of service receipts, component part numbers, and ownership history.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>📦 Transport & Delivery</h2>\r\n<p>We provide global logistics support to ensure this collector-grade vehicle arrives safely at your garage:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li><strong>Enclosed Transport Only:</strong> Shipped exclusively via a climate-controlled, hard-sided enclosed vehicle transporter.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Pre-Delivery Inspection:</strong> Handed over after a thorough mechanical inspection, fluid check, and professional detail.</li>\r\n</ol>', '1967 Chevrolet Corvette Sting Ray Convertible (427/435 HP Tri-Power)', 'An iconic American masterpiece featuring a matching-numbers 427 L71 V8 engine, iconic stinger hood, and a breathtaking, award-winning frame-off restoration.', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '1967-chevrolet-corvette-sting-ray-convertible-427-435-hp-tri-power', '', '', '2026-07-13 16:49:29', '2026-07-13 10:49:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?post_type=product&#038;p=70', 0, 'product', '', 1),
